  { q: "If a robot kills a person, who is ethically responsible according to the class discussions?", correct: "The creators and programmers of the AI system, and the organizations that deployed it.", opts: ["The creators and programmers of the AI system, and the organizations that deployed it.", "The robot itself.", "The victim for getting in the way.", "Nobody; it's an 'act of God.'"] },
  { q: "Finally, why is 'Professional Objectivity' important in software evaluation?", correct: "It ensures that software is judged on its merits rather than personal gain or bias.", opts: ["It ensures that software is judged on its merits rather than personal gain or bias.", "It makes the evaluation faster.", "It is required by the building code.", "It allows you to ignore the user's needs."] }
